Fly. you fools!

1317
02:27:43.606 --> 02:27:45.767
No!

1318
02:27:51.948 --> 02:27:54.109
Aragorn!

1319
02:28:51.340 --> 02:28:54.173
Legolas. get them up.

1320
02:28:58.306 --> 02:29:00.137
Give them a moment. for pity's sake!

1321
02:29:00.308 --> 02:29:03.926
By nightfall. these hills will
be swarming with orcs.

1322
02:29:04.145 --> 02:29:07.478
We must reach the woods of I othlorien.

1323
02:29:08.357 --> 02:29:11.690
Come. Boromir. Legolas.
Gimli. get them up.

1324
02:29:13.196 --> 02:29:15.357
On your feet. Sam.

1325
02:29:15.698 --> 02:29:17.188
Frodo?

1326
02:29:19.285 --> 02:29:20.991
Frodo!

1327
02:30:13.506 --> 02:30:16.043
Stay close. young hobbits!

1328
02:30:16.759 --> 02:30:20.923
They say that a great sorceress
lives in these woods.

1329
02:30:21.138 --> 02:30:23.675
An elf-witch

1330
02:30:24.225 --> 02:30:27.092
of terrible power.

1331
02:30:27.645 --> 02:30:29.852
All who look upon her...

1332
02:30:30.064 --> 02:30:31.850
Fall under her spell.

1333
02:30:32.066 --> 02:30:33.351
Female voice: Frodo!

1334
02:30:35.611 --> 02:30:37.647
And are never seen again.

1335
02:30:37.863 --> 02:30:42.357
Female voice: Your coming to us is
as the footsteps of doom.

1336
02:30:42.577 --> 02:30:46.286
You bring great evil here.
ring-beatrer.

1337
02:30:46.455 --> 02:30:48.241
Sam: Mr Frodo?

1338
02:30:53.546 --> 02:30:59.132
Well. here's one dwarf
she won't ensnare so easily.

1339
02:30:59.302 --> 02:31:03.887
I have the eyes of a hawk
and the ears of a fox.

1340
02:31:11.564 --> 02:31:16.149
The dwarf breathes so loud.
we could have shot him in the dark.

1341
02:31:34.295 --> 02:31:36.581
So much for the legendary courtesy
of the elves!

1342
02:31:36.756 --> 02:31:38.667
Speak words we can all understand!

1343
02:31:38.841 --> 02:31:43.426
We have not had dealings
with the dwarves since the dark days.

1344
02:31:43.679 --> 02:31:46.216
And you know what this dwarf
says to that?

1345
02:31:53.147 --> 02:31:55.103
That was not so courteous.

1346
02:32:01.656 --> 02:32:05.695
You bring great evil with you.

1347
02:32:07.453 --> 02:32:09.660
You can go no further.

1348
02:32:46.909 --> 02:32:49.571
(Gandalf's death was not in vain.

1349
02:32:50.705 --> 02:32:52.570
Nor would he have you give up hope.

1350
02:32:54.083 --> 02:32:57.416
You carry a heavy burden. Frodo.

1351
02:32:58.295 --> 02:33:01.412
Don't carry the weight of the dead.

1352
02:33:04.385 --> 02:33:06.421
You will follow me.

1353
02:33:18.107 --> 02:33:20.098
Caras galadhon.

1354
02:33:20.735 --> 02:33:23.693
The heart of elvendom on earth.

1355
02:33:23.863 --> 02:33:29.529
Realm of the lord celeborn
and of Galadriel. lady of light.

1356
02:34:48.531 --> 02:34:51.648
The enemy knows you have entered here.

1357
02:34:52.326 --> 02:34:57.491
What hope you had in secrecy
is now gone.

1358
02:34:59.208 --> 02:35:03.668
Eight there are here. yet nine there
were set out from rivendell

1359
02:35:03.921 --> 02:35:05.707
tell me. where is Gandalf?

1360
02:35:05.923 --> 02:35:09.040
For I much desire to speak with him.

1361
02:35:09.218 --> 02:35:12.005
I can no longer see him from afar.

1362
02:35:12.888 --> 02:35:18.053
Galadriel: Gandalf the grey did not
pass the borders of this land.

1363
02:35:18.310 --> 02:35:20.722
He has fallen into shadow.

1364
02:35:25.442 --> 02:35:29.936
He was taken by both shadow and flame.

1365
02:35:31.574 --> 02:35:35.317
A balrog of morgoth.

1366
02:35:36.036 --> 02:35:39.403
For we went needlessly
into the net of Moria.

1367
02:35:41.542 --> 02:35:44.750
Needless were none of the deeds
of Gandalf in life.

1368
02:35:45.421 --> 02:35:48.709
We do not yet know his full purpose.

1369
02:35:53.470 --> 02:35:57.759
Do not let the great emptiness
of khazad-dam fill your heart...

1370
02:35:58.058 --> 02:36:00.390
Gimli. son of gloin.

1371
02:36:01.395 --> 02:36:04.933
For the world has grown
full of peril...

1372
02:36:06.400 --> 02:36:09.062
And in all lands

1373
02:36:09.236 --> 02:36:12.728
love is now mingled with grief.

1374
02:36:25.377 --> 02:36:28.084
What now becomes of this fellowship?

1375
02:36:28.631 --> 02:36:31.623
Without Gandalf. hope is lost.

1376
02:36:34.595 --> 02:36:37.883
The quest stands upon the edge
of a knife.

1377
02:36:38.057 --> 02:36:41.140
Stray but a little and it will fall...

1378
02:36:41.894 --> 02:36:44.727
To the ruin of all

1379
02:36:49.068 --> 02:36:54.904
yet hope remains
while the company is true.

1380
02:36:56.450 --> 02:37:01.160
Do not let your hearts be troubled.
Go now and rest

1381
02:37:01.622 --> 02:37:05.285
for you are weary with sorrow
and much toil

1382
02:37:07.544 --> 02:37:09.660
tonight. you will sleep...

1383
02:37:09.838 --> 02:37:13.251
Galadriel:
Welcome. Frodo of the shire...

1384
02:37:14.843 --> 02:37:16.629
One who has seen the eye!

1385
02:37:31.276 --> 02:37:33.858
A lament for Gandalf

1386
02:37:41.120 --> 02:37:42.656
What do they say about him?

1387
02:37:42.871 --> 02:37:45.533
I have not the heart to tell you.

1388
02:37:48.293 --> 02:37:50.534
For me. the grief is still too near.

1389
02:37:53.507 --> 02:37:56.340
I bet they don't mention his fireworks.

1390
02:37:56.510 --> 02:37:59.547
There should be a verse about them.

1391
02:38:03.100 --> 02:38:05.091
The finest rockets ever seen

1392
02:38:06.228 --> 02:38:09.061
they burst in stars of blue and green

1393
02:38:09.982 --> 02:38:13.395
or after thunder. silver showers

1394
02:38:15.904 --> 02:38:18.691
came falling like a rain of flowers

1395
02:38:18.866 --> 02:38:22.734
oh. that doesn't do them justice
by a long road.

1396
02:38:33.589 --> 02:38:36.251
Aragorn: Take some rest.

1397
02:38:36.425 --> 02:38:39.132
These borders are well-protected.

1398
02:38:39.344 --> 02:38:41.881
I will find no rest here.

1399
02:38:44.725 --> 02:38:47.717
I heard her voice inside my head.

1400
02:38:47.936 --> 02:38:51.679
She spoke of my father
and the fall of gondor.

1401
02:38:51.899 --> 02:38:57.360
She said to me.
"even now there is hope left."

1402
02:38:58.739 --> 02:39:01.572
But I cannot see it.

1403
02:39:02.910 --> 02:39:05.401
It is long since we had any hope.

1404
02:39:15.589 --> 02:39:17.705
My father is a noble man.

1405
02:39:18.467 --> 02:39:20.708
But his rule is failing...

1406
02:39:21.053 --> 02:39:26.468
And our people lose faith.

1407
02:39:27.893 --> 02:39:31.431
He looks to me to make things right.
and I would do it.

1408
02:39:31.605 --> 02:39:35.143
I would see the glory
of gondor restored

1409
02:39:37.986 --> 02:39:40.978
have you ever seen it. aragorn?

1410
02:39:41.615 --> 02:39:43.651
The white tower of ecthelion.

1411
02:39:43.826 --> 02:39:47.660
Glimmering like a spike
of Pearl and silver.

1412
02:39:48.330 --> 02:39:51.822
Its banners caught high
in the morning breeze.

1413
02:39:54.711 --> 02:39:56.667
Have you ever been called home...

1414
02:39:56.839 --> 02:40:00.798
By the clear ringing
of silver trumpets?

1415
02:40:01.426 --> 02:40:04.668
I have seen the white city...

1416
02:40:05.013 --> 02:40:06.503
Long ago.

1417
02:40:07.474 --> 02:40:12.434
One day. our paths will lead us there.

1418
02:40:13.355 --> 02:40:16.313
And the tower guard
shall take up the call:

1419
02:40:16.775 --> 02:40:20.108
"The lords of gondor have returned

1420
02:41:27.304 --> 02:41:29.841
Will you look into the mirror?

1421
02:41:30.015 --> 02:41:31.551
What will I see?

1422
02:41:34.519 --> 02:41:36.851
Fven the wisest cannot tell

1423
02:41:37.773 --> 02:41:39.604
for the mirror...

1424
02:41:39.816 --> 02:41:42.353
Shows many things.

1425
02:41:45.364 --> 02:41:47.730
Things that were...

1426
02:41:47.950 --> 02:41:50.532
Things that are...

1427
02:41:51.286 --> 02:41:53.242
And some things...

1428
02:41:56.833 --> 02:42:00.121
That have not yet come to pass.

1429
02:43:22.711 --> 02:43:25.544
I know what it is you saw.

1430
02:43:27.966 --> 02:43:30.457
For it is also in my mind.

1431
02:43:32.220 --> 02:43:36.304
It is what will come to pass
if you should fail.

1432
02:43:38.685 --> 02:43:43.554
The fellowship is breaking.
It is already begun.

1433
02:43:44.191 --> 02:43:47.479
He will try to take the ring.

1434
02:43:47.694 --> 02:43:49.685
You know of whom I speak.

1435
02:43:50.697 --> 02:43:55.361
One by one. it will destroy them all.

1436
02:43:56.870 --> 02:43:59.327
Frodo: If you ask it of me...

1437
02:43:59.706 --> 02:44:02.743
I will give you the one ring.

1438
02:44:03.835 --> 02:44:05.996
You offer it to me freely.

1439
02:44:10.592 --> 02:44:14.505
I do not deny that my heart
has greatly desired this.

1440
02:44:20.894 --> 02:44:24.182
In place of a dark lord.
you would have a queen...

1441
02:44:24.606 --> 02:44:28.440
Not dark but beautiful.
and terrible as the dawn!

1442
02:44:29.069 --> 02:44:32.106
Treacherous as the seal

1443
02:44:32.614 --> 02:44:37.529
stronger than the foundations
of the earth!

1444
02:44:37.994 --> 02:44:40.360
All shall love me

1445
02:44:40.580 --> 02:44:43.413
and despair.

1446
02:44:57.514 --> 02:45:01.803
I pass the test. I will diminish...

1447
02:45:02.102 --> 02:45:04.559
And go into the west...

1448
02:45:04.771 --> 02:45:09.231
- And remain Galadriel.
- I cannot do this alone.

1449
02:45:12.821 --> 02:45:16.985
You are a ring-bearer. Frodo.
To bear a ring of power...

1450
02:45:17.909 --> 02:45:19.399
Is to be alone.

1451
02:45:22.747 --> 02:45:25.489
This is nenya.
the ring of adamant.

1452
02:45:25.667 --> 02:45:27.282
And I am its keeper.

1453
02:45:30.505 --> 02:45:34.123
This task was appointed to you.

1454
02:45:35.177 --> 02:45:38.044
And if you do not find a way...

1455
02:45:39.264 --> 02:45:41.255
No one will

1456
02:45:41.641 --> 02:45:44.804
then I know what I must do

1457
02:45:45.479 --> 02:45:46.685
it's just...

1458
02:45:49.941 --> 02:45:52.182
I'm afraid to do it.

1459
02:45:55.697 --> 02:46:00.817
Even the smallest person can change
the course of the future.

1460
02:46:06.166 --> 02:46:11.877
Do you know how the orcs
first came into being?

1461
02:46:12.672 --> 02:46:16.005
They were elves once.

1462
02:46:17.177 --> 02:46:20.510
Taken by the dark powers...

1463
02:46:20.722 --> 02:46:23.885
Tortured and mutilated.

1464
02:46:24.226 --> 02:46:29.516
A ruined and terrible form of life.

1465
02:46:29.814 --> 02:46:31.645
And now

1466
02:46:33.109 --> 02:46:34.974
perfected.

1467
02:46:35.695 --> 02:46:38.858
My fighting uruk-hai...

1468
02:46:40.825 --> 02:46:43.157
Whom do you serve?

1469
02:46:43.370 --> 02:46:45.861
Saruman!

1470
02:47:06.726 --> 02:47:10.184
Hunt them down. Do not stop
until they are found.

1471
02:47:10.397 --> 02:47:13.264
You do not know pain.
You do not know fear.

1472
02:47:13.525 --> 02:47:16.437
You will taste man-flesh!

1473
02:47:21.533 --> 02:47:25.242
One of the halflings carries
something of great value.

1474
02:47:25.412 --> 02:47:29.576
Bring them to me alive and unspoiled.

1475
02:47:31.418 --> 02:47:32.703
Kill the others.

1476
02:47:51.896 --> 02:47:57.311
Celeborn: Never before have we clad
strangers in the garb of our own people.

1477
02:47:58.445 --> 02:48:02.279
May these cloaks help shield you
from unfriendly eyes.

1478
02:48:09.456 --> 02:48:10.992
I embas.

1479
02:48:11.249 --> 02:48:12.830
Elvish waybread.

1480
02:48:15.337 --> 02:48:18.329
One small bite is enough to fill
the stomach of a grown man.

1481
02:48:24.846 --> 02:48:26.802
How many did you eat?

1482
02:48:26.973 --> 02:48:28.634
Four.

1483
02:48:34.439 --> 02:48:37.039
Celeborn: Every league you travel south.
the danger will increase.

1484
02:48:37.233 --> 02:48:41.351
Mordor orcs now hold the eastern shore
of the anduin.

1485
02:48:41.529 --> 02:48:44.020
Nor will you find safety
oh the western bank.

1486
02:48:44.240 --> 02:48:48.028
Strange creatures bearing the white hand
have been seen on our borders.

1487
02:48:48.244 --> 02:48:53.329
Seldom do orcs journey in the open
under the sun. yet these have done so.

1488
02:49:05.929 --> 02:49:07.406
By river you have the chance...

1489
02:49:07.430 --> 02:49:10.638
Of outrunning the enemy
to the falls of rauros.

1490
02:49:27.909 --> 02:49:32.744
Galadriel: My gift for you. Legolas.
is a bow of the galadhrim.

1491
02:49:32.997 --> 02:49:36.489
Worthy of the skill
of our woodland kin.

1492
02:49:41.881 --> 02:49:44.338
These are the daggers of the noldorin.

1493
02:49:44.509 --> 02:49:48.502
They have already seen service in war.

1494
02:49:48.680 --> 02:49:50.921
Do not fear. young peregrin took.

1495
02:49:51.099 --> 02:49:54.432
You will find your courage.

1496
02:49:56.312 --> 02:49:58.268
And for you. samwise gamgee...

1497
02:49:58.440 --> 02:50:01.022
Elven rope made of hithlain.

1498
02:50:01.192 --> 02:50:03.308
Thank you. my lady.

1499
02:50:05.113 --> 02:50:08.446
Have you run out
of those nice. shiny daggers?

1500
02:50:14.914 --> 02:50:17.951
And what gift would a dwarf ask
of the elves?

1501
02:50:18.126 --> 02:50:20.242
Nothing.

1502
02:50:20.879 --> 02:50:24.212
Except to look upon the lady
of the galadhrim one last time

1503
02:50:24.841 --> 02:50:30.052
for she is more fair
than all the jewels beneath the earth.

1504
02:50:37.103 --> 02:50:38.639
Actually...

1505
02:50:38.855 --> 02:50:40.470
There was one thing.

1506
02:50:41.316 --> 02:50:43.978
No. no. I'm talking nonsense.
It's quite impossible.

1507
02:50:44.152 --> 02:50:46.939
Stupid to ask.

1508
02:50:49.491 --> 02:50:51.607
Galadriel:
I have nothing greater to give...

1509
02:50:51.785 --> 02:50:55.369
Than the gift you already bear.

1510
02:51:21.022 --> 02:51:24.105
That choice is yet before her.

1511
02:51:24.692 --> 02:51:27.604
You have your own choice to make.
aragorn.

1512
02:51:27.946 --> 02:51:33.782
To rise above the height of all
your fathers since the days of elendil...

1513
02:51:33.952 --> 02:51:38.286
Or to fall into darkness
with all that is left of your kin.

1514
02:52:05.859 --> 02:52:09.067
Farewell. Frodo Baggins.

1515
02:52:09.237 --> 02:52:12.650
I give you the light of earendil...

1516
02:52:13.408 --> 02:52:15.740
Our most beloved star.

1517
02:52:24.878 --> 02:52:29.247
May it be a light for you
in dark places...

1518
02:52:29.507 --> 02:52:33.591
When all other lights go out.

1519
02:52:42.437 --> 02:52:45.600
Gimli: I have taken my worst wound
at this parting...

1520
02:52:46.232 --> 02:52:50.521
Naving looked my last upon that
which is fairest

1521
02:52:51.279 --> 02:52:54.612
henceforth I will call nothing fair
unless it be her gift to me.

1522
02:52:54.866 --> 02:52:56.777
What was her gift?

1523
02:52:56.993 --> 02:53:01.908
I asked her for one hair
from her golden head.

1524
02:53:02.707 --> 02:53:05.574
She gave me three.

1525
02:54:47.729 --> 02:54:51.187
Gollum. He has tracked us since Moria.

1526
02:54:54.902 --> 02:54:58.019
I had hoped we would lose him
on the river.

1527
02:54:58.239 --> 02:55:01.402
But he's too clever a waterman.

1528
02:55:02.243 --> 02:55:05.576
And if he alerts the enemy
to our whereabouts

1529
02:55:05.747 --> 02:55:07.988
it will make the crossing
even more dangerous.

1530
02:55:08.166 --> 02:55:10.248
Sam: Have some food. Mr. Frodo.

1531
02:55:10.418 --> 02:55:13.501
- No. Sam.
- You haven't eaten anything all day.

1532
02:55:13.671 --> 02:55:16.754
You're not sleeping. neither.
Don't think I haven't noticed.

1533
02:55:17.717 --> 02:55:20.709
- Mr. Frodo...
- I'm all right.

1534
02:55:20.887 --> 02:55:22.047
But you're not.

1535
02:55:22.346 --> 02:55:24.837
I'm here to help you.

1536
02:55:25.016 --> 02:55:26.722
I promised Gandalf that I would.

1537
02:55:32.690 --> 02:55:35.432
You can't help me. Sam.

1538
02:55:37.570 --> 02:55:39.276
Not this time.

1539
02:55:42.200 --> 02:55:44.282
Get some sleep.

1540
02:55:50.541 --> 02:55:52.748
Minas tirith is the safer road.

1541
02:55:53.294 --> 02:55:56.036
You know that.
From there we can regroup.

1542
02:55:56.714 --> 02:55:58.955
Strike out for mordor from a place
of strength.

1543
02:55:59.300 --> 02:56:02.167
There is no strength in gondor
that can avail us.

1544
02:56:02.637 --> 02:56:04.628
You were quick enough to trust
the elves.

1545
02:56:06.474 --> 02:56:09.307
Have you so little faith
in your own people?

1546
02:56:09.477 --> 02:56:12.469
Yes. there is weakness.
There is frailty.

1547
02:56:12.688 --> 02:56:15.976
But there is courage also.
and honor to be found in men.

1548
02:56:16.234 --> 02:56:18.441
But you will not see that.

1549
02:56:18.778 --> 02:56:20.188
You are afraid!

1550
02:56:20.446 --> 02:56:22.983
All your life. you have hidden
in the shadows

1551
02:56:23.282 --> 02:56:26.740
scared of who you are.
of what you are.

1552
02:56:29.163 --> 02:56:33.497
I will not lead the ring within
a hundred leagues of your city.

1553
02:56:45.346 --> 02:56:46.711
Frodo.

1554
02:56:48.599 --> 02:56:50.089
The argonath.

1555
02:56:53.521 --> 02:56:57.264
Long have I desired
to look upon the kings of old.

1556
02:56:58.025 --> 02:56:59.936
My kin.

1557
02:58:18.940 --> 02:58:21.101
We cross the lake at nightfall.

1558
02:58:21.359 --> 02:58:23.941
Hide the boats and continue on foot.

1559
02:58:24.111 --> 02:58:27.603
- We approach mordor from the north.
- Oh. yes?

1560
02:58:28.032 --> 02:58:31.866
Just a simple matter of finding
our way through emyn mull...

1561
02:58:32.036 --> 02:58:35.278
An impassable labyrinth
of razor-sharp rocks.

1562
02:58:35.456 --> 02:58:38.573
And after that. it gets even better.

1563
02:58:38.960 --> 02:58:43.920
Festering. stinking marshland
as far as the eye can see.

1564
02:58:44.090 --> 02:58:45.455
That is our road.

1565
02:58:47.051 --> 02:58:50.259
I suggest you take some rest
and recover your strength. master dwarf.

1566
02:58:50.471 --> 02:58:52.211
Recover my...

1567
02:58:55.226 --> 02:58:57.217
We should leave now. No.

1568
02:58:57.395 --> 02:59:01.855
Orcs patrol the eastern shore.
We must wait for cover of darkness.

1569
02:59:02.066 --> 02:59:05.479
It is not the eastern shore
that worries me.

1570
02:59:05.736 --> 02:59:09.729
A shadow and a threat
has been growing in my mind.

1571
02:59:10.241 --> 02:59:14.405
Something draws near.
I can feel it.

1572
02:59:16.414 --> 02:59:21.374
Recover strength?
Pay no heed to that. young hobbit.

1573
02:59:21.877 --> 02:59:23.583
Where's Frodo?

1574
02:59:49.196 --> 02:59:51.107
Boromir:
None of us should wander alone.

1575
02:59:52.533 --> 02:59:54.615
You. least of all.

1576
02:59:54.827 --> 02:59:57.284
So much depends on you.

1577
02:59:58.331 --> 03:00:00.287
Frodo?

1578
03:00:07.423 --> 03:00:09.960
I know why you seek solitude.

1579
03:00:10.676 --> 03:00:14.134
You suffer. I see it day by day.

1580
03:00:14.930 --> 03:00:17.967
You sure you do not suffer needlessly?

1581
03:00:19.560 --> 03:00:22.176
There are other ways. Frodo.

1582
03:00:22.438 --> 03:00:26.226
- Other paths that we might take.
- I know what you would say.

1583
03:00:26.484 --> 03:00:30.227
It would seem like wisdom
but for the warning in my heart.

1584
03:00:30.488 --> 03:00:33.571
Warning? Against what?

1585
03:00:33.741 --> 03:00:35.857
We're all afraid. Frodo.

1586
03:00:36.077 --> 03:00:39.695
But to let that fear drive us.
to destroy what hope we have...

1587
03:00:39.955 --> 03:00:43.698
- Don't you see that is madness?
- There is no other way.

1588
03:00:45.503 --> 03:00:48.836
I ask only for the strength
to defend my people!

1589
03:00:50.383 --> 03:00:52.465
- If you would but lend me the ring.
- No.

1590
03:00:53.677 --> 03:00:57.340
- Why do you recoil? I am no thief.
- You are not yourself.

1591
03:00:59.183 --> 03:01:02.516
What chance do you think you have?

1592
03:01:02.686 --> 03:01:07.350
They will find you.
They will take the ring.

1593
03:01:07.608 --> 03:01:11.271
And you will beg for death
before the end!

1594
03:01:13.406 --> 03:01:15.522
You fool!

1595
03:01:15.699 --> 03:01:19.692
It is not yours. save by unhappy chance!
It could have been mine.

1596
03:01:19.870 --> 03:01:22.703
It should be mine! Give it to me!

1597
03:01:22.873 --> 03:01:24.204
- Give it to me!
- No!

1598
03:01:24.375 --> 03:01:26.206
- Give it to me!
- No.

1599
03:01:33.884 --> 03:01:35.875
I see your mind.

1600
03:01:36.137 --> 03:01:39.049
You will take the ring to Sauron!

1601
03:01:39.265 --> 03:01:41.130
You will betray us!

1602
03:01:41.392 --> 03:01:44.555
You'll go to your death.
and the death of us alll

1603
03:01:45.020 --> 03:01:48.638
curse you!
Curse you and all the halflings!

1604
03:01:55.739 --> 03:01:57.229
Frodo?

1605
03:02:01.579 --> 03:02:03.160
Frodo.

1606
03:02:07.084 --> 03:02:09.075
What have I done?

1607
03:02:09.295 --> 03:02:11.035
Please. Frodo.

1608
03:02:11.255 --> 03:02:13.917
Frodo. I'm sorry!

1609
03:02:14.133 --> 03:02:15.998
Frodo!

1610
03:03:02.473 --> 03:03:03.883
Frodo?

1611
03:03:05.142 --> 03:03:08.225
- It has taken Boromir.
- Where is the ring?

1612
03:03:08.479 --> 03:03:10.219
Stay away!

1613
03:03:10.648 --> 03:03:12.229
Frodo!

1614
03:03:14.485 --> 03:03:18.319
- I swore to protect you.
- Can you protect me from yourself?

1615
03:03:27.998 --> 03:03:30.489
Would you destroy it?

1616
03:03:35.506 --> 03:03:37.417
Voice of the ring: Aragorn.

1617
03:03:40.844 --> 03:03:43.176
Aragorn.

1618
03:03:45.015 --> 03:03:46.846
Flessar

1619
03:03:54.525 --> 03:03:57.858
I would have gone with you to the end.

1620
03:03:58.529 --> 03:04:01.362
Into the very fires of mordor.

1621
03:04:04.702 --> 03:04:05.862
I know.

1622
03:04:08.372 --> 03:04:13.787
Look after the others. Especially Sam.
He will not understand.

1623
03:04:17.548 --> 03:04:19.288
Go. Frodo!

1624
03:04:22.303 --> 03:04:23.793
Run.

1625
03:04:24.054 --> 03:04:25.715
Run!

1626
03:04:50.247 --> 03:04:51.908
Mr. Frodo!

1627
03:05:01.216 --> 03:05:02.956
Find the halfling!

1628
03:05:04.595 --> 03:05:07.132
Find the halfling!

1629
03:05:10.601 --> 03:05:12.262
Flendill

1630
03:05:18.776 --> 03:05:20.357
Aragorn. go!

1631
03:05:42.049 --> 03:05:43.380
Pippin: Frodo!

1632
03:05:43.967 --> 03:05:45.548
Hide here. Quick!

1633
03:05:46.178 --> 03:05:47.634
Come on!

1634
03:05:50.140 --> 03:05:52.131
What's he doing?

1635
03:05:56.397 --> 03:05:58.388
He's leaving.

1636
03:06:03.153 --> 03:06:06.065
- No!
- Pippin!

1637
03:06:10.994 --> 03:06:13.326
Merry: Run. Frodo. Go on!

1638
03:06:13.914 --> 03:06:16.997
- Hey! Hey. you!
- Over here!

1639
03:06:17.418 --> 03:06:18.999
- Over here!
- This way!

1640
03:06:29.847 --> 03:06:32.179
- It's working!
- I know it's working! Run!

1641
03:07:27.571 --> 03:07:30.608
- The horn of gondor.
- Boromir.

1642
03:08:13.700 --> 03:08:14.815
Run!

1643
03:11:46.413 --> 03:11:48.028
No

1644
03:11:51.877 --> 03:11:54.914
- They took the little ones.
- Hold still.

1645
03:11:55.255 --> 03:11:57.337
Frodo where is Frodo?

1646
03:12:01.344 --> 03:12:03.926
Then you did what I could not.

1647
03:12:04.931 --> 03:12:08.264
I tried to take the ring from him.

1648
03:12:08.769 --> 03:12:13.058
- The ring is beyond our reach now.
- Forgive me.

1649
03:12:13.273 --> 03:12:15.559
I did not see it.

1650
03:12:15.776 --> 03:12:18.939
- I have failed you all.
- No. Boromir.

1651
03:12:19.404 --> 03:12:21.941
You fought bravely.

1652
03:12:22.240 --> 03:12:24.902
You have kept your honor.

1653
03:12:25.452 --> 03:12:27.408
Boromir: I eave it.

1654
03:12:27.746 --> 03:12:29.782
It is over.

1655
03:12:30.957 --> 03:12:36.247
The world of men will fall.
And all will come to darkness

1656
03:12:36.671 --> 03:12:39.663
and my city to ruin.

1657
03:12:43.762 --> 03:12:46.469
I do not know what strength
is in my blood...

1658
03:12:46.640 --> 03:12:50.633
But I swear to you.
I will not let the white city fall...

1659
03:12:51.645 --> 03:12:54.136
Nor our people fail.

1660
03:12:55.148 --> 03:12:56.479
Our people.

1661
03:13:00.320 --> 03:13:02.436
Our people.

1662
03:13:24.177 --> 03:13:27.169
I would have followed you. my brother.

1663
03:13:28.723 --> 03:13:30.714
My captain.

1664
03:13:33.353 --> 03:13:35.309
My king.

1665
03:13:54.958 --> 03:13:57.199
Be at peace...

1666
03:13:57.544 --> 03:13:59.535
Son of gondor.

1667
03:14:16.062 --> 03:14:19.395
They will look for his coming
from the white tower.

1668
03:14:19.900 --> 03:14:22.892
But he will not return.

1669
03:14:46.092 --> 03:14:48.083
Frodo!

1670
03:15:07.572 --> 03:15:10.814
Frodo:
I wish the ring had never come to me.

1671
03:15:12.118 --> 03:15:15.110
I wish none of this had happened.

1672
03:15:18.083 --> 03:15:20.825
Gandalf: So do all who live
fo see such times.

1673
03:15:21.044 --> 03:15:24.457
But that is not for them to decide.

1674
03:15:24.631 --> 03:15:27.293
All you have to decide...

1675
03:15:27.550 --> 03:15:32.294
Is what to do with the time
that is given to you.

1676
03:16:01.126 --> 03:16:03.162
Frodo. no!

1677
03:16:03.670 --> 03:16:05.001
Frodo!

1678
03:16:05.839 --> 03:16:08.501
- Mr. Frodo!
- No. Sam.

1679
03:16:12.012 --> 03:16:14.003
Go back. Sam!

1680
03:16:14.514 --> 03:16:18.098
- I'm going to mordor alone.
- Of course you are.

1681
03:16:18.310 --> 03:16:21.143
And I'm coming with you!

1682
03:16:21.604 --> 03:16:24.016
You can't swim!

1683
03:16:27.819 --> 03:16:29.525
Sam!

1684
03:16:35.118 --> 03:16:36.403
Sam!

1685
03:17:17.369 --> 03:17:20.076
I made a promise. Mr. Frodo.

1686
03:17:20.413 --> 03:17:24.747
A promise:
"Don't you leave him. samwise gamgee."

1687
03:17:25.877 --> 03:17:28.459
And I don't mean to.

1688
03:17:28.755 --> 03:17:30.916
I don't mean to.

1689
03:17:32.592 --> 03:17:34.423
Sam.

1690
03:17:49.275 --> 03:17:50.936
Come on.

1691
03:18:19.431 --> 03:18:23.970
Hurry! Frodo and Sam
have reached the eastern shore.

1692
03:18:38.825 --> 03:18:43.819
- You mean not to follow them.
- Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands.

1693
03:18:47.292 --> 03:18:52.161
Then it has all been in vain.
The fellowship has failed.

1694
03:19:04.017 --> 03:19:07.180
Not if we hold true to each other.

1695
03:19:08.521 --> 03:19:13.015
We will not abandon merry and pippin
to torment and death

1696
03:19:14.027 --> 03:19:19.272
not while we have strength left.
Leave all that can be spared behind.

1697
03:19:20.533 --> 03:19:22.569
We travel light.

1698
03:19:22.785 --> 03:19:24.696
I et us hunt some orc.

1699
03:19:27.665 --> 03:19:29.701
Yes!

1700
03:19:48.686 --> 03:19:50.096
Frodo: Mordor.

1701
03:19:50.730 --> 03:19:54.097
I hope the others find a safer road.

1702
03:19:55.068 --> 03:19:57.605
Strider will look after them.

1703
03:19:58.571 --> 03:20:01.904
I don't suppose
we'll ever see them again.

1704
03:20:02.242 --> 03:20:04.699
We may yet. Mr. Frodo.

1705
03:20:04.911 --> 03:20:06.401
We may.

1706
03:20:08.540 --> 03:20:09.575
Sam.

1707
03:20:13.211 --> 03:20:15.827
I'm glad you are with me.

